body_html:
Hmm. I usually just load all of my data in via pandas as opposed to using the functions provided by tensorflow. However, looking at what you just shot me, I think the problem is in the target_dtype value--you have it set for np.float32 where you want it as np.int16 or np.int64

Try changing that and see what happens!

body:
Hmm. I usually just load all of my data in via pandas as opposed to using the functions provided by tensorflow. However, looking at what you just shot me, I think the problem is in the target_dtype value--you have it set for np.float32 where you want it as np.int16 or np.int64 

Try changing that and see what happens!
